sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM student_transfers 
WHERE transfer_status = 'approved';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT student_id) 
FROM student_scholarships 
WHERE status = 'awarded';

external_knowledge:
- 'Approved transfer' refers to a credit transfer agreement that has been officially accepted;
- 'Credits transferred' refers to the number of academic credits moved from one institution to another;
- 'More than one approved transfer' means the student has had multiple credit transfer agreements accepted.

- 'Fall 2022' refers to the academic semester in the year 2022;
- 'Tuition fee' is the amount charged for the program;
- 'Program' refers to the academic program the student is enrolled in.

- "remaining fee" refers to the difference between the average tuition fee of the student's program and the total amount of scholarships awarded to the student;
- "total scholarships" is the sum of all scholarships awarded to a student;
- "average tuition fee" is the mean tuition fee for all students in the same program.

sql:
SELECT MAX(tuition_fee) 
FROM programs 
WHERE duration_years = (SELECT MAX(duration_years) FROM programs);

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT st.student_id) AS total_students_involved
FROM student_transfers st
JOIN student_scholarships ss ON st.student_id = ss.student_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Shining stars' refers to students who excel in both academic performance and financial aid;
- 'Completed courses' are courses that students have finished and received a final grade for;
- 'Most generous scholarships' are the highest amounts awarded to students.

- 'Generous scholarships' refers to scholarships with amounts greater than 4000;
- 'Prestigious universities' refers to universities located in the United Kingdom;
- 'More than 10,000 in financial aid' refers to the total sum of scholarship amounts exceeding 10000.

- "program" is metaphorically referred to as a "garden";
- "university" is metaphorically referred to as a "gardener";
- "students" are metaphorically referred to as "flowers".

sql:
SELECT amount
FROM student_scholarships
WHERE status = 'awarded';

external_knowledge:
- "High GPA requirement" refers to programs with a minimum GPA requirement greater than 3.0;
- "Approved transfer status" refers to transfers that have been approved;
- "Most recent transfers" and "most recent enrollments" are determined by the latest dates in the respective tables.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(student_id) 
FROM students 
WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_transfers);

external_knowledge:
- 'Engineering students' refers to students enrolled in a B.Eng. program;
- 'Pending transfer' indicates the transfer status of the student is 'pending';
- 'Awarded scholarship' means the scholarship status is 'awarded'.

- 'awarded' status indicates that the scholarship has been granted to the student;
- 'amount' refers to the monetary value of the scholarship received by the student;
- 'program_name' is the name of the educational program the student is enrolled in.

- The Government of Malaysia provides scholarships to eligible students;
- A minimum GPA of 3.0 is considered a high academic standard;
- Students from Malaysia are those whose nationality is listed as Malaysia.
